  <sect1>
    <title>Activation Keys Best Practices</title>
    <para>There are a several things which should be kept in mind when creating activation keys. The
      following list provides insight on naming and which packages should be included.<itemizedlist>
        <listitem>
          <para>Channels to be included:<itemizedlist>
              <listitem>
                <para>suse-manager-tools</para>
              </listitem>
            </itemizedlist></para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
          <para>Typical packages to be included:<itemizedlist>
              <listitem>
                <para>osad(pushing tasks)<itemizedlist>
                    <listitem>
                      <para>Installs python-jabberpy and pyxml as dependencies</para>
                    </listitem>
                  </itemizedlist></para>
              </listitem>
              <listitem>
                <para> rhncfg-actions (Remote Command, Configuration Managment) <itemizedlist>
                    <listitem>
                      <para>Installs rhncfg and rhncfg-client as dependencies</para>
                    </listitem>
                  </itemizedlist></para>
              </listitem>
            </itemizedlist></para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
          <para>Create naming schemes for types of activation keys and combine them<itemizedlist>
              <listitem>
                <para>OS naming (mandatory)</para>
              </listitem>
              <listitem>
                <para>Server type naming</para>
              </listitem>
              <listitem>
                <para>Location based naming</para>
              </listitem>
              <listitem>
                <para>Custom naming</para>
              </listitem>
            </itemizedlist></para>
        </listitem>
      </itemizedlist></para>
    <note>
      <title>Specific Base Channel Assignment</title>
      <para>OS keys must have a specific base channel assigned to it or &susemgr; will be unable to
        assign specific stages. Also all non-OS keys must have <replaceable>SUSE Manager Default
        </replaceable> as their base channel.</para>
    </note>
  </sect1>

